included.name: Group identification and prejudice distribution: Implications for diversity.
included.description: We summarized current research on the relationship between group identification, the importance of a group membership to one's sense of self, and both the experience and the perpetration of bias.

included.name: Do women who succeed in male-dominated domains help other women?: The moderating role of group identification.
included.description: It is often expected that the first women to advance in male-dominated fields will promote other women who follow them. We found that women's gender identification (the extent to which their gender is central to their self-concept) predicted whether they would show this expected pattern or the opposite (favoring men). This pattern only emerged when they advanced in the context of underrerpresentation.

included.name: The ironic consequences of Obama's election: Decreased support for social justice.
included.description: We longitudinally examined attitdues towards social justice immediately before and after Obama's election. As hypothesized, the election of Barack Obama ironically resulted in decreased support for social justice programs that could benefit other racial minorities.
